                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0090F/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-08T10:00:00+03:06"
                            >February 8, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Plans for consular representation in Dhahran referred to in Department’s 17,
                    January 29, 3 p.m., discussed with Amir Faisal February 6.</p>
                <p>His personal reaction appeared favorable though he promised nothing more than a
                    reply after having referred matter to King.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
